The paper deals with the analysis of a two-hop cellular system using mathematical tools from stochastic geometry and point process theory. The focus is on the spatial distribution of the nodes and the performance of different relaying schemes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Signal Processing (cs.SI), Game Theory (cs.GT), or Mathematical Analysis (cs.MA) sub-categories.
